"{\"uid\": \"themedialine.org-headlines-saboteurs-strike-french-rail-on-eve-of-paris-olympics-sparking-security-scramble\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Saboteurs targeted France's TGV high-speed train network, disrupting major rail lines just hours before the Paris Olympics opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 140, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 25, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999944481675767, \"rank\": 5.296846872921188e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 28, \"end\": 31, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TGV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"TGV\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TGV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TGV\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The state-owned railway operator, SNCF, reported vandalism on signal boxes along key routes, including Paris to Lille, Bordeaux, and Strasbourg, and an attempted sabotage on the Paris-Marseille line.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 175, \"end\": 179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNCF\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"SNCF\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNCF\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNCF\"}, {\"begin\": 244, \"end\": 249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999993179, \"rank\": 6.05052532626063e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 253, \"end\": 258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9996910230949669, \"rank\": 0.00029884226485518933, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}, {\"begin\": 260, \"end\": 268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\", \"score\": 0.9936268703717512, \"rank\": 0.006414000422266772, \"text\": \"Bordeaux\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\"}, {\"begin\": 274, \"end\": 284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strasbourg-Ville_station\", \"score\": 0.988945606316337, \"rank\": 0.011177958878499423, \"text\": \"Strasbourg\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strasbourg-Ville_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strasbourg-Ville_station\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No group has claimed responsibility for the attacks, which utilized a sophisticated knowledge of the railway system, hinting at the possibility of involvement by leftist or environmental terrorists.\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 540, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, security sources stress that evidence is still being gathered, and conclusions remain premature.\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 646, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"accurate, fearless journalism.\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 678, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But we can not do it alone.\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The incident has not only caused significant disruption, stranding hundreds of thousands of travelers, but has also intensified security concerns as France hosts the Olympics.\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 857, \"end\": 863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999944481675767, \"rank\": 5.296846872921188e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prime Minister Gabriel Attal urged caution and refrained from speculating on the perpetrators, emphasizing the coordinated and knowledgeable nature of the sabotage.\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 1048, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Attal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Amidst these security challenges, France is ramping up its efforts to ensure safety, deploying a robust force of 45,000 police, 10,000 soldiers, and additional private security personnel for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1084, \"end\": 1090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999944481675767, \"rank\": 5.296846872921188e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony is expected to draw a global audience, with more than 300,000 spectators anticipated along the River Seine.\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1383, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1371, \"end\": 1382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}]}"